Learniverse

Learniverse is an e-learning platform that provides a comprehensive learning experience for users. This project is a learning project, and its primary goal is to demonstrate the implementation of various features and technologies in a real-world application.

Getting Started

To get started with the project, follow these steps:

Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/Anand-m-Mishra/learniverse-backend.git
Install the required dependencies: npm install
Start the server: npm run dev

Features

Authentication

User registration and login using JSON Web Tokens (JWT)
Password hashing and salting using bcrypt
Token verification and refresh token implementation
for better undestanding check: https://github.com/Anand-m-Mishra/learniverse-backend/blob/main/api-documentation/Authentication.doc.txt
for understanding user creatinn check: https://github.com/Anand-m-Mishra/learniverse-backend/blob/main/api-documentation/user-backend-api.txt

completing tasks added to todo and some pre defined tasks

for understanding the todo apis read:  https://github.com/Anand-m-Mishra/learniverse-backend/blob/main/api-documentation/todo-backend-api.txt



